commit.message:
CI: update actions to v4

It is needed because of the warning: "Please update the following
actions to use Node.js 20"
docs: update rounding function description

builtins: align all implementations of __round_varying

Make all implementations of __round_varying across different targets and
types to actually do roundeven
Remove dispatch-no-spr

CI: upload alloy_results logs on failure

Split also x86 and x86-64 linux jobs to different one matrix jobs.
CI: convert LLVM 17 rebuild job to matrix job
CI: provide defaults to LLVM reusable rebuild job
CI: name artifacts with -lto when LTO is enabled
superbuild: fix clang_rt.profile path for LLVM 17

SwitchBoolSize: introduce two different SwitchBool* functions

SwitchBoolToStorageType converts to storage bool type whereas
SwitchBoolToMaskType convers to internal bool (mask) type.

They are wrappers above SwitchBoolSize function that has now extra bool
flag to choose the proper sign/zero extension mode. The previous logic
of distinguishing between bool type flavors (based on comparison of type
size) was wrong because storage and internal bool types can have same
type width.

This also fixes typecasting of short bool vectors in I1VecToBoolType.
SwitchBoolSize also can convert bool short vector types, i.e., array of
vectors of bools.
opt.cpp: fix memorySSA enablement under debugPM

Rename Print() method for debuggers

It is needed to avoid name conflict that happens with overloaded virtual
method Print(Indent). Debuggers struggle (at least gdb) to resolve it.
opt.cpp: remove unused alloca definition
lCreateConstExpr: allocate vals on the heap

Fix ISPC build with LLVM 18.1 and trunk

llvm_patches: add x86-isel fix

This backported patch fixes generation of redundant vmovd, vpinsrd
instructions.
